<plot>In this program celebrating the Ford Motor Company's 75th anniversary, various expressions of creativity are honored. Arthur Miller introduces a scene from "Death of a Salesman" performed by Edward Asner and Martin Sheen; Tennessee Williams and Neil Simon also introduce scenes from their plays. Other parts of the program feature comedy and musical performances, as well as interviews with prominent figures such as astronaut Neil Armstrong.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?015639</url></doc>
